## ðŸ§© iii. Simulate to Find the Number of Packets Dropped by TCP/UDP

ðŸŽ¯ *Goal:* Compare TCP and UDP behavior.

*Setup:*

* Scenario Type: *Wired*
* *Nodes:* 4 nodes â†’ n0, n1, n2, n3
* *Links:*

* n0 â†” n2 (for TCP) â†’ Duplex, 1 Mb
* n1 â†” n3 (for UDP) â†’ Duplex, 1 Mb
* n2 â†” n3 (bottleneck link) â†’ Duplex, 0.5 Mb
* *Agents:*

* TCP agent on n0 â†’ TCP Sink on n3
* UDP agent on n1 â†’ Null agent on n3
* *Applications:*

* FTP on TCP connection
* CBR (Constant Bit Rate) on UDP connection
* *Simulation time:* 10s
* *Output Files:* tcp_udp.tr, tcp_udp.nam

âœ… *Expected result:* UDP drops more packets than TCP (youâ€™ll confirm with awk).

