## ðŸ§© iv. Simulate to Find the Number of Packets Dropped due to Congestion

ðŸŽ¯ *Goal:* Show congestion (too many sources sending to one destination).

*Setup:*

* Scenario Type: *Wired*
* *Nodes:* 5 nodes â†’ n0, n1, n2, n3, n4
* *Links:*

* n0 â†” n3 â†’ Duplex, 1 Mb
* n1 â†” n3 â†’ Duplex, 1 Mb
* n2 â†” n3 â†’ Duplex, 1 Mb
* n3 â†” n4 â†’ Duplex, *0.5 Mb* (bottleneck link)
* *Agents:*

* TCP on n0, n1, and n2 (sources)
* TCP Sink on n4 (destination)
* *Applications:* FTP on each TCP source
* *Simulation time:* 10â€“15s
* *Output Files:* congestion.tr, congestion.nam

âœ… *Expected result:* Many packets dropped at the bottleneck link (n3â†”n4) â€” congestion drops.

